2. Iterate through the string and update the counts accordingly.
3. Use a while loop to continue swapping the counts until they are equal.
4. Return the number of swaps needed.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n) because we iterate through the string once. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a single integer array to store the counts. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few operations and does not consume much energy.

